Vienna Airport cancels passenger calls
Mr. Max Maier, please come to Gate 24.
There will no longer be any such announcements at Vienna-Schwechat Airport in the future.
A lot of the loudspeaker announcements are thus eliminated - the noise level should be significantly reduced.
Creating a more relaxed atmosphere is the goal of this innovation.
As Airport spokesman Peter Kleemann told Radio Wien, Vienna Airport is following an international trend with the discontinuation of announcements that affect individual people.
Among other things, the airports in Copenhagen, Frankfurt and Dubai are already giving up the noisy calls.
Due to the elimination of these announcements - on average, around 200 personal calls through the speakers sound in a day - it should be quieter at the airport in the future.
"It has also been shown in the experience that these individual announcements were relatively little perceived, but all other information about changed flight climbing or departure times also goes down a bit here," says Kleemann in a conversation with the radio station.
