George Kerevan: European unbundling gives the Scots a choice
A new day, a new frightening story about independence.
This time we are warned that an independent Scotland is needed to join the Schengen area as a condition for EU membership.
This provides the keyword for stories about passport controls in Berwick and a barbed wire-secured border along the Hadrian's Wall.
