I don't know if that's what I should have expected.
Whether I should have understood at the age of 18 that the government work could be contrary to the previous political campaigns.
Obviously, the MP’s office is not a predictable course, as an opposition party and random events such as the Newtown massacre shape the public discussion.
But when I look at the above examples, they seem to have been largely chosen by the government itself.
